for `BOOT_COMPLETED`. Checkout the documentation [here][1]. 

As far as I see everything else should be ok.

**p.s.**: if you want to receive a broadcast event for incoming calls, use permission

    &lt;uses-permission android:name=&quot;android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE&quot; /&gt;

and declare your intent filter with 

    &lt;receiver 
      android:name=&quot;com.ram.tapdetector.CallManager&quot;
      android:enabled=&quot;true&quot;&gt;   
        &lt;intent-filter
          android:priority=&quot;1000&quot;&gt;
            &lt;action android:name=&quot;android.intent.action.PHONE_STATE&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;/intent-filter&gt;
    &lt;/receiver&gt;

Check this nice [tutorial][2] for more.


  [1]: http://developer.android.com/reference/android/Manifest.permission.html#RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETED
  [2]: https://web.archive.org/web/20210127130519/http://www.tutorialforandroid.com/2009/01/get-phone-state-when-someone-is-calling_22.html

